description.originalText: Alona was great. My 5mo loved playing with her and she was kind enough to tidy up the house which was much appreciated.

bio.experienceSummary: I was raised with an autistic brother so I have first hand experience with taking care of children with special needs, and I have been a camp counselor for many years for children as young as three to as old as 12. I also have experience taking care of infants, I want to own my own daycare in the future and have taken a few education courses so that I may be able to teach younger children as well. I am available anytime and the best place to reach me is my cellphone.

Hi There! I'm 24 and I was raised in Rahway, NJ. I am currently a full time aesthetician student looking for a job that work with my schedule(Mon-Fri. 9am-3:30pm). I've worked with kids since I could remember from my nephew and nieces to my cousins to my neighbors kids to daycares. I've always loved working with kids, watching them grow and learn new things is very special to me. 
When working with kids I make sure I create a safe and fun environment, i'm very patient thanks to my past daycare jobs and working with infants, and I show children how to be creative by planning fun activities or crafts.
During my free time I like to go shopping and hangout with my family. 

I'd describe my personality as patient, friendly, and caring 

I started working with kids when I was about 14 years old and I started with taking care of my nephew and nieces.


One thing you should know about me is i'm a fast learner and reliable

Hi! I'm Rhea, I'm a 2nd year doctorate student studying occupational therapy. I'm hoping to become a pediatric occupational therapist! I've been a babysitter for two different families for the past 3 years. For one of them, I take care of a 2-year-old and a 6-year-old. Duties include: taking care of them during date night, night time routine/putting them to bed, meal prep, taking the kids to afterschool activities or to the park, and morning/afternoon pickup/drop off. For my other job, I take care of a 10-year-old. My duties there include: taking her into NYC for afterschool activities, homework help, light housekeeping, school pick up, running errands, etc. As I said I've been working for these families for 3 years so I have plenty of experience. In addition to that, this past summer I worked part time taking care of a 4-month-old & 6-month-old baby.

Looking forward to hearing from you!

description.originalText:
We couldn’t be more grateful for the incredible care Rhea provided for our baby. From the very first day, she brought warmth, love, and dedication into our home. Her presence was not just about watching our little one; it was about truly engaging with them. She filled each day with creativity, patience, and genuine affection.

Her ability to connect with our baby was remarkable. Whether it was through playful interactions, or just quiet moments of being present, she always knew how to make our child feel secure and cherished. It was evident that she has incredible work ethic and punctuality.

What impressed us the most was her patience. Navigating the ups and downs of infancy can be challenging, but she handled every situation with grace and understanding. Her calm demeanor helped create a nurturing environment where our baby could thrive.

We felt so at ease knowing our child was in such loving hands. Her commitment to our family went beyond the basics. We cannot recommend her highly enough. Thank you for everything—you truly made a difference in our lives! Also, we miss you :(!

bio.experienceSummary: It's always been my passion to work with children. I started babysitting when I was 14. Throughout high school, I babysat for 3 families both part-time and full-time. At 16, I started working at my community center as a babysitter and assistant teacher. I helped with homework and engaged in creative play. In the fall of 2017, I started attending Seton Hall University and started working for a babysitting agency. I'm still looking for local families to babysit for on an occasional basis (not looking for after school). I have been background checked and fingerprinted, and I'm CPR and First Aid certified.

Hello, my name is Gianna, I am 23 years old and I am a college student. Ever since I was younger I've always enjoyed helping people. I have experience watching over children and helping with their needs. In the summer of 2017, I was given a chance to work around children and since then I've spent my summers as a counselor, teacher, and assistant working with different age groups in various environments such as camps and daycares. I have over 7 years of experience. I often travel through the boroughs to try new restaurants, visit new places or go to dance classes so I'm open to babysitting anywhere! I like to spend my free time reading, dancing, cooking, doing yoga and trying new hobbies such as roller skating. I would describe myself as being kind, creative, respectful and adventurous. I'm open to working late and I'm great with pets. I'm looking forward to being an addition to your family and creating a safe place and comfortable atmosphere for your children to thrive in.

description.displayText: Gianna and I worked together at a day care and she's shown understanding, patience and empathy for children. You can tell that she has passion for her job,  and that she puts the kids she takes care of first especially when it comes to their safety, as well as their development in manners, boundaries, as well as other areas like speech.

description.originalText: Maria is super proactive and hands on. She’s really great with our baby, you can tell she genuinely loves being a mom and adores babies. She’s very attentive to his needs, great with playing with him and reading books to him, and she maintains a safe space for him. And she’s very supportive in all aspects- keeping his playroom tidy, bottle cleanup, daycare bag prep, etc. I strongly recommend her.

bio.experienceSummary:
As a nurturing and experienced childcare provider, my passion lies in fostering children's growth and development. With three years of experience, I've had the privilege of positively impacting the lives of young minds. My patient, creative, and approachable nature allows me to connect with children effortlessly. I prioritize open communication with parents through daily reports, verbal updates, and regular check-ins.

My comfort in enforcing household rules ensures a safe and structured environment for the children in my care. From outdoor adventures to educational games, I relish engaging children in a variety of activities that promote physical, mental, and social development.

As a holder of an ECE certification and First Aid training, I'm committed to providing a nurturing and stimulating environment for your child. Whether it's assisting with meal preparation, light housekeeping, or supervising swimming, I'm here to support your family's needs.

I am a professional chef and baker. I am very passionate, patient, friendly and loving. I have two bachelors degrees, one in philosophy and the other in literature section french. I also have a diploma to translate from french to Arabic and Arabic to french.
